manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: MAXIMUM STRENGTH DOSE(1) IMMUNE SUPPORT+ Vitamin C is an antioxidant that helps neutralize free radicals in the body. These gummies provide 1000 mg of Vitamin C per serving to help support the immune system and a healthy upper respiratory tract.+ (1)Compared to Nature Made Vitamin C Gummies. HELPS SUPPORTS A HEALTHY UPPER RESPIRATORY TRACT+ At 1000 mg per serving, these Vitamin C gummies help support a healthy upper respiratory tract.+ DELICIOUS VITAMIN C GUMMIES FOR ADULTS MADE WITH PECTIN Featuring a delicious tangerine flavor and made with pectin, these gummies are a great-tasting way for adults to take their vitamins. Adults, chew 4 gummies daily. HIGH QUALITY INGREDIENTS Made from carefully selected ingredients under strict manufacturing practices to meet our high quality standards. No artificial flavors – natural fruit flavors, no synthetic dyes – color derived from natural source, no high fructose corn syrup, no artificial sweeteners, gluten free.

Understanding Vitamin C Vitamin C (also known as ascorbic acid) is a water-soluble essential nutrient that your body needs to consume and replenish every day. Vitamin C is found in citrus fruits like oranges, lemons, grapefruit, and limes. It’s also found in tomatoes, red peppers, broccoli, and strawberries. Almost 50% of U.S. adults are not getting enough Vitamin C through their daily food intake (2). If you just want to make sure you’re getting what your body needs, Vitamin C supplements may help. (2) Reider, Carroll A et al. “Inadequacy of Immune Health Nutrients: Intakes in US Adults, the 2005-2016 NHANES.” Nutrients vol. 12,6 1735. 10 Jun. 2020, doi:10.3390/nu12061735 Vitamin C plays an important role in supporting the immune system. As an antioxidant, it helps neutralize free radicals in the body, and it may help aid in iron absorption in the body, too.+

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worked for me
reviews.reviewText: I was advised to consume Vitamin C gummies as part of a strategy to combat nicotine cravings. So, I ended up ordering these.The citrus flavor is a strong slap in the face, while the texture is soft yet grainy due to the sugar(?) that clings to them. They vaguely remind me of the orange gummy chews you could pick up at a gasoline station, but are softer than them.
